title: P006T
treatment_protocol_ch1: No treatment prior to expression profiling analysis was performed.
growth_protocol_ch1: Biospies from patients not cell lines were used for analyses
extract_protocol_ch1: Biopsies were immediately stored in RNAlater (Qiagen, Hilden, Germany). Subsequently, RNA and DNA was isolated using TRIzol (Invitrogen, Carlsbad, CA) according to the manufacturer´s instructions.  Nucleic acid quantity, quality and purity were determined using a spectrophotometer (Nanodrop, Rockland, DE) and a 2100 Bioanalyzer (Agilent Technologies, Palo Alto, CA).
label_protocol_ch1: 1 µg of total RNA was labeled with Cy3 using the Low RNA Input Fluorescent Linear Amplification Kit according to the manufacturer's recommendations (Agilent Technologies, Santa Clara, CA). Quantity and efficiency of the labeled amplified cRNA were determined using the NanoDrop ND-1000 UV-VIS Spectrophotometer version 3.2.1.
hyb_protocol: 1.5 mg of Cy3-labeled cRNA was hybridized to an oligonucleotide-based Whole Human Genome Microarray (4x44K, Agilent Technologies) and incubated at 65˚C for 17 hours.
scan_protocol: Slides were washed and scanned using an Agilent G2565BA scanner.
description: Human pretherapeutic rectal cancer patient biopsy sample P006T
data_processing: Raw data were extracted using the Feature Extraction software version 9.1 (Agilent Technologies). Median signal intensities from the Feature Extraction Software were converted to log2 and quantile normalized using the R package “limma”.

Nucleic acid quantity, quality and purity were determined using a spectrophotometer (Nanodrop, Rockland, DE) and a 2100 Bioanalyzer (Agilent Technologies, Palo Alto, CA).
label_protocol_ch1: 1 µg of total RNA was labeled with Cy3 using the Low RNA Input Fluorescent Linear Amplification Kit according to the manufacturer's recommendations (Agilent Technologies, Santa Clara, CA). Quantity and efficiency of the labeled amplified cRNA were determined using the NanoDrop ND-1000 UV-VIS Spectrophotometer version 3.2.1.
hyb_protocol: 1.5 mg of Cy3-labeled cRNA was hybridized to an oligonucleotide-based Whole Human Genome Microarray (4x44K, Agilent Technologies) and incubated at 65˚C for 17 hours.
scan_protocol: Slides were washed and scanned using an Agilent G2565BA scanner.
description: Human pretherapeutic rectal cancer patient biopsy sample P081T
data_processing: Raw data were extracted using the Feature Extraction software version 9.1 (Agilent Technologies). Median signal intensities from the Feature Extraction Software were converted to log2 and quantile normalized using the R package “limma”.

label_protocol_ch1: 1 µg of total RNA was labeled with Cy3 using the Low RNA Input Fluorescent Linear Amplification Kit according to the manufacturer's recommendations (Agilent Technologies, Santa Clara, CA). Quantity and efficiency of the labeled amplified cRNA were determined using the NanoDrop ND-1000 UV-VIS Spectrophotometer version 3.2.1.
hyb_protocol: 1.5 mg of Cy3-labeled cRNA was hybridized to an oligonucleotide-based Whole Human Genome Microarray (4x44K, Agilent Technologies) and incubated at 65˚C for 17 hours.
scan_protocol: Slides were washed and scanned using an Agilent G2565BA scanner.
description: Human pretherapeutic rectal cancer patient biopsy sample P123T
data_processing: Raw data were extracted using the Feature Extraction software version 9.1 (Agilent Technologies). Median signal intensities from the Feature Extraction Software were converted to log2 and quantile normalized using the R package “limma”.

label_protocol_ch1: 1 µg of total RNA was labeled with Cy3 using the Low RNA Input Fluorescent Linear Amplification Kit according to the manufacturer's recommendations (Agilent Technologies, Santa Clara, CA). Quantity and efficiency of the labeled amplified cRNA were determined using the NanoDrop ND-1000 UV-VIS Spectrophotometer version 3.2.1.
hyb_protocol: 1.5 mg of Cy3-labeled cRNA was hybridized to an oligonucleotide-based Whole Human Genome Microarray (4x44K, Agilent Technologies) and incubated at 65˚C for 17 hours.
scan_protocol: Slides were washed and scanned using an Agilent G2565BA scanner.
description: Human pretherapeutic rectal cancer patient biopsy sample P007M
data_processing: Raw data were extracted using the Feature Extraction software version 9.1 (Agilent Technologies). Median signal intensities from the Feature Extraction Software were converted to log2 and quantile normalized using the R package “limma”.

label_protocol_ch1: 1 µg of total RNA was labeled with Cy3 using the Low RNA Input Fluorescent Linear Amplification Kit according to the manufacturer's recommendations (Agilent Technologies, Santa Clara, CA). Quantity and efficiency of the labeled amplified cRNA were determined using the NanoDrop ND-1000 UV-VIS Spectrophotometer version 3.2.1.
hyb_protocol: 1.5 mg of Cy3-labeled cRNA was hybridized to an oligonucleotide-based Whole Human Genome Microarray (4x44K, Agilent Technologies) and incubated at 65˚C for 17 hours.
scan_protocol: Slides were washed and scanned using an Agilent G2565BA scanner.
description: Human pretherapeutic rectal cancer patient biopsy sample P083M
data_processing: Raw data were extracted using the Feature Extraction software version 9.1 (Agilent Technologies). Median signal intensities from the Feature Extraction Software were converted to log2 and quantile normalized using the R package “limma”.

label_protocol_ch1: 1 µg of total RNA was labeled with Cy3 using the Low RNA Input Fluorescent Linear Amplification Kit according to the manufacturer's recommendations (Agilent Technologies, Santa Clara, CA). Quantity and efficiency of the labeled amplified cRNA were determined using the NanoDrop ND-1000 UV-VIS Spectrophotometer version 3.2.1.
hyb_protocol: 1.5 mg of Cy3-labeled cRNA was hybridized to an oligonucleotide-based Whole Human Genome Microarray (4x44K, Agilent Technologies) and incubated at 65˚C for 17 hours.
scan_protocol: Slides were washed and scanned using an Agilent G2565BA scanner.
description: Human pretherapeutic rectal cancer patient biopsy sample P124M
data_processing: Raw data were extracted using the Feature Extraction software version 9.1 (Agilent Technologies). Median signal intensities from the Feature Extraction Software were converted to log2 and quantile normalized using the R package “limma”.
